text.tspan: Can we talk a bit more about amazing things y
ou can do with Paradox Generator. It can gene
rate random strings from input configuration
files. They are quite easy to use and leave r
oom for a lot of costumization. You can defin
e your own templates which can be used for ge
neration of random numbers, items from lists
and such inside of localization. Localization
allows you to write your text generation conf
iguration only once and translate it to as ma
ny languages as you like (and know). The enti
re format using xml files is very straight fo
rward and simple when you get to know it. All
you need to do to learn how to use this progr
am efficiently is go to the GitHub repository
and run over the tutorial. It explains how to
use and create your own generators, items, te
mplates, functions and localization. Main goa
l I had while writing this program was to kee
p it as flexible as possible while not overco
,plicating it by forcing users to enter big a
mounts of data in order to do something very
simple and straightforward. Random function f
or example allows you to generate random inte
gers, floats, years (which adds BC suffix if
generated year is negative), dice rolls and o
ne of the most useful features is random enum
eration which picks a random child item. All
items can also have custom weight which gives
you more control over how things are generate
d. If you read this entire text, I congradula
te you on wasting your time!
